# Codex Plugin Operation Guide

> The following rules apply only when the Codex plugin (`openai/codex-plugin-cc`) is installed.
> Simple tasks (single-file/few-line changes, config edits, doc updates) can be handled directly by Claude.

## Architecture

Claude Code acts as the commander (design, integration, final judgment).
Codex acts as the executor (code generation, review, refactoring, testing, debugging, security audits).
Claude always verifies and integrates Codex output before reporting to the user.

## Delegation Criteria

### Delegate to Codex when:
- New code generation expected to be 20+ lines
- Changes spanning multiple files
- Code review (Codex is more thorough)
- Test code creation
- Refactoring / optimization
- Root cause analysis of bugs
- Security vulnerability scanning

### Claude handles directly:
- Single-file, few-line changes
- Config file edits (YAML, JSON, TOML, etc.)
- Documentation / README updates
- Git operations (commit, branch, merge)
- User communication / Q&A

## Available Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `/codex:review` | Standard code review |
| `/codex:adversarial-review` | Skeptical challenge review |
| `/codex:rescue` | Hand work off to Codex |
| `/codex:status` | Check running job status |
| `/codex:result` | Retrieve job results |
| `/codex:cancel` | Cancel a running job |
| `/codex:setup` | Check/configure installation |

## Security Notes

- Never include API keys or secrets in Codex prompts
- Always perform security reviews on Codex-generated code
